# apt-control - move packages in to your apt repository based on gemspec-esque version specifications

Requirements:
 - reprepro based apt site
 - directory full of builds
 - ruby1.8 and rubygems
 - jabber server (for notifications)

# install

gem install apt-control-{some-version}.gem

# using

Get a dump of the state of your repository

apt_control \
 --apt-site-dir=/var/www/apt.site.com \
 --control-file=/etc/apt.site.com/apt-control.ini \
 --build-archive-dir=/var/www/apt.site.com/builds \
 status


Watch your build directory for new packages to arrive, moving them in to
apt as they do

apt_control \
 --apt-site-dir=/var/www/apt.site.com \
 --control-file=/etc/apt.site.com/apt-control.ini \
 --build-archive-dir=/var/www/apt.site.com/builds \
 --jabber-id=aptbot@jabber.server.com --jabber-password=hushhush \
 --jabber-chatroom-id=notify@conference.jabber.server.com/aptbot \
 watch
